of the largest towns in east bhutan. paro - the location of the international airport and taktsang monastery. punakha - a former winter capital of bhutan. it still hosts the monastic body in winter. phuentsholing - a town on the indian border. the point of entry for travelers arriving by bus from west bengal. samdrup jongkhar - an administrative town in the southeast. it is the point of entry for travelers arriving from [assam]. trashigang - a picturesque administrative town in the east. trongsa - a small administrative town famous for its dzong and the tower of trongsa other destinations[edit] 